00:39:21.060 --> 00:39:22.060
There we are.

00:39:22.060 --> 00:39:23.060
Do you want to stop for a minute?

00:39:23.060 --> 00:39:24.060
Mm-hm.

00:39:24.060 --> 00:39:26.060
Right, ask you,

00:39:26.060 --> 00:39:28.060
could you describe,

00:39:28.060 --> 00:39:30.060
you know, what were your first impressions

00:39:30.060 --> 00:39:33.060
when you walked into that factory?

00:39:33.060 --> 00:39:35.060
What it looked like,

00:39:35.060 --> 00:39:37.060
the sights, the smells,

00:39:37.060 --> 00:39:40.060
the whole kind of thing?

00:39:40.060 --> 00:39:42.060
Well, I walked in as though

00:39:42.060 --> 00:39:44.060
I was on top of the world,

00:39:44.060 --> 00:39:46.060
and I could see glass

00:39:46.060 --> 00:39:48.060
and women,

00:39:48.060 --> 00:39:50.060
and some of them were saying hi to me,

00:39:50.060 --> 00:39:54.060
and Mr. Degarthwood actually took me through,

00:39:54.060 --> 00:39:56.060
that's the boss,

00:39:56.060 --> 00:39:58.060
to the section,

00:39:58.060 --> 00:40:01.060
and he introduced me to the supervisor,

00:40:01.060 --> 00:40:04.060
and she then introduced me to all the girls

00:40:04.060 --> 00:40:06.060
and sat me down,

00:40:06.060 --> 00:40:11.060
and I was there working,

00:40:11.060 --> 00:40:13.060
trying to do what she's telling me to do,

00:40:13.060 --> 00:40:15.060
because she was showing me,

00:40:15.060 --> 00:40:17.060
and she was telling me to carry on,

00:40:17.060 --> 00:40:19.060
and then when the bell went,

00:40:19.060 --> 00:40:22.060
I thought, oh, it's break time,

00:40:22.060 --> 00:40:24.060
and I went to the toilet,

00:40:24.060 --> 00:40:26.060
went upstairs with all the girls,

00:40:26.060 --> 00:40:28.060
and had a chat.

00:40:28.060 --> 00:40:31.060
It was really, really wonderful.

00:40:31.060 --> 00:40:33.060
Did you know any of the women there?

00:40:33.060 --> 00:40:35.060
Oh, yeah, yes, a load of them,

00:40:35.060 --> 00:40:37.060
a load of them,

00:40:37.060 --> 00:40:39.060
because they all lived round here.

00:40:39.060 --> 00:40:42.060
They've known me ever since school,

00:40:42.060 --> 00:40:44.060
or I've met them in town.

00:40:44.060 --> 00:40:46.060
I knew most of them.

00:40:46.060 --> 00:40:48.060
Did you socialise with them?

00:40:48.060 --> 00:40:50.060
Yes, but not a lot,

00:40:50.060 --> 00:40:53.060
because I had my daughter,

00:40:53.060 --> 00:40:55.060
and I also didn't have enough money

00:40:55.060 --> 00:40:57.060
coming from the factory

00:40:57.060 --> 00:41:00.060
that I took on little jobs in those days.

00:41:00.060 --> 00:41:03.060
You were able to get away with some of the jobs.

00:41:03.060 --> 00:41:05.060
No, no, no.

00:41:05.060 --> 00:41:08.060
Because I used to work for Goli's Ice Cream,

00:41:08.060 --> 00:41:10.060
Rugby Club,

00:41:10.060 --> 00:41:12.060
I loved the rugby club,

00:41:12.060 --> 00:41:15.060
but that was my second job, that was.

00:41:15.060 --> 00:41:19.060
And my social life was working.

00:41:19.060 --> 00:41:21.060
When you were at work,

00:41:21.060 --> 00:41:24.060
were you allowed to talk and play music

00:41:24.060 --> 00:41:26.060
and things like that?

00:41:26.060 --> 00:41:28.060
We were allowed to have music

00:41:28.060 --> 00:41:30.060
when Atwoods were there,

00:41:30.060 --> 00:41:32.060
because I used to take my own records in,

00:41:32.060 --> 00:41:34.060
the 45s.

00:41:34.060 --> 00:41:37.060
I would be singing away and still working,

00:41:37.060 --> 00:41:39.060
because it made us happy.

00:41:39.060 --> 00:41:41.060
We worked better with music.

00:41:41.060 --> 00:41:43.060
You cut it off, we didn't.

00:41:43.060 --> 00:41:45.060
It slowed production up.

00:41:45.060 --> 00:41:48.060
So do you remember what songs they were?

00:41:48.060 --> 00:41:53.060
They were the 60s and the 70s songs.

00:41:53.060 --> 00:41:56.060
Actually, I've still got them,

00:41:56.060 --> 00:41:58.060
but I can't remember the...

00:41:58.060 --> 00:42:00.060
I was going to ask if you had any favourites.

00:42:00.060 --> 00:42:02.060
Yes, like...

00:42:02.060 --> 00:42:04.060
What's his name?

00:42:04.060 --> 00:42:06.060
He's coloured.

00:42:06.060 --> 00:42:08.060
It's the wrong word to say, I think.

00:42:08.060 --> 00:42:10.060
Black man, was he?

00:42:10.060 --> 00:42:12.060
Yes.

00:42:12.060 --> 00:42:14.060
Everything's a winner, baby,

00:42:14.060 --> 00:42:16.060
that's the truth, that one.

00:42:16.060 --> 00:42:18.060
I can't remember his name.

00:42:18.060 --> 00:42:20.060
Oh, I don't remember that.

00:42:20.060 --> 00:42:22.060
Oh, fun that was.

00:42:22.060 --> 00:42:24.060
Loads.

00:42:24.060 --> 00:42:26.060
I took once in a rugby club,

00:42:26.060 --> 00:42:28.060
sorry, rugby song,

00:42:28.060 --> 00:42:30.060
big album,

00:42:30.060 --> 00:42:34.060
and you had to think of the words

00:42:34.060 --> 00:42:36.060
when they said the song.

00:42:36.060 --> 00:42:38.060
You put your own...

00:42:38.060 --> 00:42:41.060
The words were cut out.

00:42:41.060 --> 00:42:43.060
Of course, the boss came through

00:42:43.060 --> 00:42:45.060
with some visitors

00:42:45.060 --> 00:42:47.060
and he was by my bench

00:42:47.060 --> 00:42:49.060
catching hold of the phone

00:42:49.060 --> 00:42:52.060
and he said, put the record off now.

00:42:52.060 --> 00:42:54.060
I felt so embarrassed

00:42:54.060 --> 00:42:56.060
because it was my record.

00:42:56.060 --> 00:42:58.060
Was it rude?

00:42:58.060 --> 00:43:00.060
Yes. They say the words

00:43:00.060 --> 00:43:02.060
and the rude words wouldn't be there.

00:43:02.060 --> 00:43:04.060
You had to...

00:43:04.060 --> 00:43:06.060
Imagine them.

00:43:06.060 --> 00:43:08.060
Yes.

00:43:08.060 --> 00:43:10.060
It was funny.

00:43:10.060 --> 00:43:12.060
I got told off for doing some work.

00:43:12.060 --> 00:43:14.060
I did a load of

00:43:14.060 --> 00:43:16.060
Concord necklaces

00:43:16.060 --> 00:43:18.060
and out of all those trays

00:43:18.060 --> 00:43:20.060
one of them went wrong.

00:43:20.060 --> 00:43:22.060
You cannot tell me

00:43:22.060 --> 00:43:24.060
that was my work

00:43:24.060 --> 00:43:26.060
that went wrong

00:43:26.060 --> 00:43:28.060
because when you do the work

00:43:28.060 --> 00:43:30.060
of all of you, it gets mixed up.

00:43:30.060 --> 00:43:32.060
So how could that

00:43:32.060 --> 00:43:34.060
be my job when all the others were all right?

00:43:34.060 --> 00:43:36.060
It wasn't too bad

00:43:36.060 --> 00:43:38.060
but he told me off.

00:43:38.060 --> 00:43:40.060
I even had some tiaras

00:43:40.060 --> 00:43:42.060
in those days

00:43:42.060 --> 00:43:44.060
that we had to form.

00:43:44.060 --> 00:43:46.060
The two women

00:43:46.060 --> 00:43:50.060
were first aid

00:43:50.060 --> 00:43:52.060
and she was in a room

00:43:52.060 --> 00:43:54.060
where she gave you...

00:43:54.060 --> 00:43:56.060
She was in a storeroom.

00:43:56.060 --> 00:43:58.060
They curled at me

00:43:58.060 --> 00:44:00.060
and they said, put the tiara on

00:44:00.060 --> 00:44:02.060
and stand up and put the tiara on.

00:44:02.060 --> 00:44:04.060
Oh yes, I did, didn't I?

00:44:04.060 --> 00:44:06.060
I was having fun. I was happy.

00:44:06.060 --> 00:44:08.060
Up came Doug

00:44:08.060 --> 00:44:10.060
and he said,

00:44:10.060 --> 00:44:12.060
I want to see your work tomorrow.

00:44:12.060 --> 00:44:14.060
We had to do a sheet.

00:44:14.060 --> 00:44:16.060
He said, I want to see

00:44:16.060 --> 00:44:18.060
how much work you did tomorrow.

00:44:18.060 --> 00:44:20.060
But I think he was put up to do it

00:44:20.060 --> 00:44:22.060
to come and frighten me

00:44:22.060 --> 00:44:24.060
because they were laughing

00:44:24.060 --> 00:44:26.060
in the corner.

00:44:26.060 --> 00:44:28.060
Next day he came along and he could see

00:44:28.060 --> 00:44:30.060
that my production was

00:44:30.060 --> 00:44:32.060
he didn't tell me off.

00:44:32.060 --> 00:44:34.060
He gave me a warning.

00:44:34.060 --> 00:44:36.060
Explain to me

00:44:36.060 --> 00:44:38.060
what a Concorde necklace is.

00:44:38.060 --> 00:44:40.060
In the Concorde days

00:44:40.060 --> 00:44:42.060
everything was

00:44:42.060 --> 00:44:44.060
Concorde paper.

00:44:44.060 --> 00:44:46.060
You could get

00:44:46.060 --> 00:44:48.060
Concorde paper.

00:44:48.060 --> 00:44:50.060
Concorde curtains

00:44:50.060 --> 00:44:52.060
were called Concorde.

00:44:52.060 --> 00:44:54.060
Because of

00:44:54.060 --> 00:44:56.060
the Concorde aeroplane.

00:44:56.060 --> 00:44:58.060
Oh, I see, right. Yes.

00:44:58.060 --> 00:45:00.060
They took the name and made it into a necklace.

00:45:02.060 --> 00:45:04.060
Can you describe it to me?

00:45:04.060 --> 00:45:06.060
It was sort of a little square

00:45:06.060 --> 00:45:08.060
dropper.

00:45:08.060 --> 00:45:10.060
Then there were two pieces that go

00:45:10.060 --> 00:45:12.060
into the chain like a V.

00:45:12.060 --> 00:45:14.060
Then there was

00:45:14.060 --> 00:45:16.060
a Concorde chain.

00:45:16.060 --> 00:45:18.060
Especially made

00:45:18.060 --> 00:45:20.060
Concorde chain it was called.

00:45:20.060 --> 00:45:22.060
Then we put a tongue in the box

00:45:22.060 --> 00:45:24.060
and extension chain on it.

00:45:24.060 --> 00:45:26.060
That was it.

00:45:26.060 --> 00:45:28.060
Where was that sold do you think?

00:45:28.060 --> 00:45:30.060
All over the world.

00:45:30.060 --> 00:45:32.060
I have a list of people that used to buy it.

00:45:32.060 --> 00:45:34.060
Especially

00:45:34.060 --> 00:45:36.060
Virgin Airways.

00:45:40.060 --> 00:45:42.060
Virgin Airways.

00:45:44.060 --> 00:45:46.060
Canada.

00:45:46.060 --> 00:45:48.060
The airlines took

00:45:48.060 --> 00:45:50.060
on all of the

00:45:50.060 --> 00:45:52.060
you see

00:45:52.060 --> 00:45:54.060
piano, sorry,

00:45:54.060 --> 00:45:56.060
what do you call it?

00:45:56.060 --> 00:45:58.060
Duty Free?

00:45:58.060 --> 00:46:00.060
We used to do masses for Duty Free.

00:46:00.060 --> 00:46:02.060
Suddenly

00:46:02.060 --> 00:46:04.060
the airlines came in.

00:46:04.060 --> 00:46:06.060
It was like a catalogue

00:46:06.060 --> 00:46:08.060
that if we

00:46:08.060 --> 00:46:10.060
produced a

00:46:10.060 --> 00:46:12.060
load of

00:46:12.060 --> 00:46:14.060
wash feathers, they would

00:46:14.060 --> 00:46:16.060
take them and

00:46:16.060 --> 00:46:18.060
dispute them.

00:46:18.060 --> 00:46:20.060
Distribute them.

00:46:20.060 --> 00:46:22.060
If they never sold, they came

00:46:22.060 --> 00:46:24.060
back.

00:46:24.060 --> 00:46:26.060
The room was full of what

00:46:26.060 --> 00:46:28.060
came back.

00:46:28.060 --> 00:46:30.060
We were mass producing for the airlines.

00:46:30.060 --> 00:46:32.060
That didn't help

00:46:32.060 --> 00:46:34.060
when they came back.

00:46:34.060 --> 00:46:36.060
Who was the tiara for then?

00:46:36.060 --> 00:46:38.060
The tiara was

00:46:38.060 --> 00:46:40.060
for any

00:46:42.060 --> 00:46:44.060
artist.

00:46:44.060 --> 00:46:46.060
If there was a bride.

00:46:46.060 --> 00:46:48.060
Wherever.

00:46:48.060 --> 00:46:50.060
I can't remember who used to

00:46:50.060 --> 00:46:52.060
make a feeling. They went to

00:46:52.060 --> 00:46:54.060
London.

00:46:54.060 --> 00:46:56.060
They would then sell them in the shops.

00:46:56.060 --> 00:46:58.060
There was a

00:46:58.060 --> 00:47:00.060
Dixon's, I believe.

00:47:00.060 --> 00:47:02.060
It was called Dixon's.

00:47:02.060 --> 00:47:04.060
There was a two name barrel

00:47:04.060 --> 00:47:06.060
in London.

00:47:06.060 --> 00:47:08.060
They took quite a lot of the work.

00:47:08.060 --> 00:47:10.060
Because the

00:47:10.060 --> 00:47:12.060
artist would go

00:47:12.060 --> 00:47:14.060
and have them

00:47:14.060 --> 00:47:16.060
for the films.

00:47:16.060 --> 00:47:18.060
Or theatres.

00:47:18.060 --> 00:47:20.060
You mentioned some of them.

00:47:20.060 --> 00:47:22.060
Can you describe?

00:47:22.060 --> 00:47:24.060
You mentioned

00:47:24.060 --> 00:47:26.060
something that's...

00:47:26.060 --> 00:47:28.060
The Pink Panther.

00:47:28.060 --> 00:47:30.060
Can you describe that piece of jewellery for me?

00:47:30.060 --> 00:47:32.060
I would call them baguettes.

00:47:32.060 --> 00:47:34.060
They were different sizes.

00:47:34.060 --> 00:47:36.060
Oblong.

00:47:36.060 --> 00:47:38.060
Like your finger.

00:47:38.060 --> 00:47:40.060
Oblong like that.

00:47:40.060 --> 00:47:42.060
Square.

00:47:42.060 --> 00:47:44.060
Oblong.

00:47:44.060 --> 00:47:46.060
They would be all the way down the necklace

00:47:46.060 --> 00:47:48.060
until they got to a

00:47:48.060 --> 00:47:50.060
centre piece.

00:47:50.060 --> 00:47:52.060
Which was shaped like a bow.

00:47:52.060 --> 00:47:54.060
Alright.

00:47:54.060 --> 00:47:56.060
Would it be a bow? It was

00:47:56.060 --> 00:47:58.060
a piece in the middle.

00:47:58.060 --> 00:48:00.060
And that would have baguettes in it as well.

00:48:00.060 --> 00:48:02.060
And what were the baguettes

00:48:02.060 --> 00:48:04.060
made out of?

00:48:04.060 --> 00:48:06.060
They were from Szywoski in Austria.

00:48:06.060 --> 00:48:08.060
Austria.

00:48:08.060 --> 00:48:10.060
Szywoski produced all these

00:48:10.060 --> 00:48:12.060
little stones.

00:48:12.060 --> 00:48:14.060
They were all different sizes.

00:48:14.060 --> 00:48:16.060
So minute.

00:48:16.060 --> 00:48:18.060
So tiny.

00:48:18.060 --> 00:48:20.060
And what were the stones, do you know?

00:48:20.060 --> 00:48:22.060
They were crystal stones.

00:48:22.060 --> 00:48:24.060
That's what they said, crystal.

00:48:24.060 --> 00:48:26.060
But they were all different colours.

00:48:26.060 --> 00:48:28.060
Whatever they wanted

00:48:28.060 --> 00:48:30.060
they would

00:48:30.060 --> 00:48:32.060
give at them size.

00:48:32.060 --> 00:48:34.060
And that was for the Pink Panther?

00:48:34.060 --> 00:48:36.060
Pink Panther, the Amore.

00:48:36.060 --> 00:48:38.060
Amore.

00:48:38.060 --> 00:48:40.060
And what was the other one you mentioned?

00:48:40.060 --> 00:48:42.060
The Amore.

00:48:42.060 --> 00:48:44.060
She wore the Berlina.

00:48:44.060 --> 00:48:46.060
Right, can you describe the Berlina to me?

00:48:46.060 --> 00:48:48.060
It had a centre piece.

00:48:48.060 --> 00:48:50.060
On it it had three little

00:48:50.060 --> 00:48:52.060
droppers, but in the middle it had an extra

00:48:52.060 --> 00:48:54.060
dropper with the dropper on.

00:48:54.060 --> 00:48:56.060
And then it had kind of

00:48:56.060 --> 00:48:58.060
flowers on the side

00:48:58.060 --> 00:49:00.060
with another dropper on the side.

00:49:00.060 --> 00:49:02.060
And then you had

00:49:02.060 --> 00:49:04.060
a chain

00:49:04.060 --> 00:49:06.060
with all the stones

00:49:06.060 --> 00:49:08.060
already in it.

00:49:08.060 --> 00:49:10.060
You counted those stones

00:49:10.060 --> 00:49:12.060
and put it onto the

00:49:12.060 --> 00:49:14.060
necklace centre.

00:49:14.060 --> 00:49:16.060
And then you had

00:49:16.060 --> 00:49:18.060
the tongue box and extension.

00:49:18.060 --> 00:49:20.060
But she also wore the earrings

00:49:20.060 --> 00:49:22.060
because you could have a

00:49:22.060 --> 00:49:24.060
flower earring with a dropper

00:49:24.060 --> 00:49:26.060
or the centre

00:49:26.060 --> 00:49:28.060
of the Berlina

00:49:28.060 --> 00:49:30.060
she was wearing.

00:49:30.060 --> 00:49:32.060
And as in one of the films

00:49:32.060 --> 00:49:34.060
I know that she was in

00:49:34.060 --> 00:49:36.060
she wore it.

00:49:36.060 --> 00:49:38.060
Did she commission that especially

00:49:38.060 --> 00:49:40.060
or was that a line you did?

00:49:40.060 --> 00:49:42.060
It was a line we did.

00:49:42.060 --> 00:49:44.060
And I believe

00:49:44.060 --> 00:49:46.060
on Coronation Street

00:49:46.060 --> 00:49:48.060
Beth Lynch

00:49:48.060 --> 00:49:50.060
was wearing the

00:49:50.060 --> 00:49:52.060
tigers.

00:49:52.060 --> 00:49:54.060
Leopards? No, the leopards.

00:49:54.060 --> 00:49:56.060
They had two heads

00:49:56.060 --> 00:49:58.060
and she was wearing them behind the bar

00:49:58.060 --> 00:50:00.060
in Coronation Street.

00:50:00.060 --> 00:50:02.060
So if you see two

00:50:02.060 --> 00:50:04.060
leopard heads

00:50:04.060 --> 00:50:06.060
that's what we produced

00:50:06.060 --> 00:50:08.060
on a chain.

00:50:08.060 --> 00:50:10.060
And when was that?

00:50:10.060 --> 00:50:12.060
When she was on

00:50:12.060 --> 00:50:14.060
Coronation Street. Before you left?

00:50:14.060 --> 00:50:16.060
Oh yes. I believe that's right

00:50:16.060 --> 00:50:18.060
before I left.

00:50:18.060 --> 00:50:20.060
I know she was wearing it.

00:50:24.060 --> 00:50:26.060
So I was going to ask you

00:50:26.060 --> 00:50:28.060
do you remember

00:50:28.060 --> 00:50:30.060
how much you were paid when you started?

00:50:30.060 --> 00:50:32.060
Yes, I can.

00:50:32.060 --> 00:50:34.060
I had £6 a week

00:50:34.060 --> 00:50:36.060
and I had to work a whole year before I had 10

00:50:36.060 --> 00:50:38.060
because when I left my old job

00:50:38.060 --> 00:50:40.060
I was getting £9 a week.

00:50:40.060 --> 00:50:42.060
That's when I left.

00:50:42.060 --> 00:50:44.060
But this one was £6.

00:50:44.060 --> 00:50:46.060
Was that because you were training do you think?

00:50:46.060 --> 00:50:48.060
Probably

00:50:48.060 --> 00:50:50.060
because they said it would take

00:50:50.060 --> 00:50:52.060
12 months.

00:50:52.060 --> 00:50:54.060
I didn't quite know

00:50:54.060 --> 00:50:56.060
if that was right.

00:50:56.060 --> 00:50:58.060
So once you trained then?

00:50:58.060 --> 00:51:00.060
I had to wait a year then.

00:51:00.060 --> 00:51:02.060
I had to wait a year though.

00:51:02.060 --> 00:51:04.060
And then you got?

00:51:04.060 --> 00:51:06.060
£10.

00:51:06.060 --> 00:51:08.060
And did you have pay rises

00:51:08.060 --> 00:51:10.060
quite regularly when you were there?

00:51:10.060 --> 00:51:12.060
It was difficult because the bosses

00:51:12.060 --> 00:51:14.060
found it difficult to make more money

00:51:14.060 --> 00:51:16.060
and he would

00:51:16.060 --> 00:51:18.060
stand in the canteen

00:51:18.060 --> 00:51:20.060
and he says

00:51:20.060 --> 00:51:22.060
we can give you a bit of a wage

00:51:22.060 --> 00:51:24.060
but it won't be much.

00:51:24.060 --> 00:51:26.060
And I would hear him jingling his

00:51:26.060 --> 00:51:28.060
keys in his pocket because he was

00:51:28.060 --> 00:51:30.060
absolutely petrified and nervous

00:51:30.060 --> 00:51:32.060
to tell us that there was

00:51:32.060 --> 00:51:34.060
not much money because the Atwoods

00:51:34.060 --> 00:51:36.060
could not actually give us

00:51:36.060 --> 00:51:38.060
a lot of money. They couldn't.

00:51:40.060 --> 00:51:42.060
How much do you think

00:51:42.060 --> 00:51:44.060
you were earning when you

00:51:44.060 --> 00:51:46.060
finally left?

00:51:46.060 --> 00:51:48.060
£152

00:51:48.060 --> 00:51:50.060
and that was because the

00:51:50.060 --> 00:51:52.060
other bosses took over and they

00:51:52.060 --> 00:51:54.060
upped our wages quite a bit.

00:51:54.060 --> 00:51:56.060
Quite a bit.

00:51:56.060 --> 00:51:58.060
What about the other bosses taking over?

00:51:58.060 --> 00:52:00.060
The secretary

00:52:00.060 --> 00:52:02.060
and the sales rep

00:52:02.060 --> 00:52:04.060
and the

00:52:04.060 --> 00:52:06.060
factory manager

00:52:06.060 --> 00:52:08.060
were asked

00:52:08.060 --> 00:52:10.060
when the Atwoods

00:52:10.060 --> 00:52:12.060
retired if they'd like

00:52:12.060 --> 00:52:14.060
to take on the business.

00:52:14.060 --> 00:52:16.060
And they did.

00:52:16.060 --> 00:52:18.060
One was in shares

00:52:18.060 --> 00:52:20.060
more than the others.

00:52:20.060 --> 00:52:22.060
And the secretary

00:52:22.060 --> 00:52:24.060
was looking after her

00:52:24.060 --> 00:52:26.060
section which was a load

00:52:26.060 --> 00:52:28.060
of secretaries.

00:52:28.060 --> 00:52:30.060
The sales rep

00:52:30.060 --> 00:52:32.060
was taking on

00:52:32.060 --> 00:52:34.060
more of a boss than

00:52:34.060 --> 00:52:36.060
the others. But the manager

00:52:36.060 --> 00:52:38.060
for the floor was still looking after

00:52:38.060 --> 00:52:40.060
us on the floor.

00:52:40.060 --> 00:52:42.060
He wasn't getting on with

00:52:42.060 --> 00:52:44.060
them at all.

00:52:44.060 --> 00:52:46.060
But it was a dog eat

00:52:46.060 --> 00:52:48.060
dog by the look of it.

00:52:48.060 --> 00:52:50.060
So do you remember what year

00:52:50.060 --> 00:52:52.060
it was that they took over?

00:52:54.060 --> 00:52:56.060
In the 80s I believe.

00:52:58.060 --> 00:53:00.060
I'd be 34

00:53:00.060 --> 00:53:02.060
and I was there

00:53:02.060 --> 00:53:04.060
in 1969.

00:53:04.060 --> 00:53:06.060
34 and

00:53:06.060 --> 00:53:08.060
would that be

00:53:08.060 --> 00:53:10.060
83?

00:53:10.060 --> 00:53:12.060
83.

00:53:12.060 --> 00:53:14.060
Yes, about the 80s.

00:53:14.060 --> 00:53:16.060
And

00:53:16.060 --> 00:53:18.060
I couldn't wait to get out of there

00:53:18.060 --> 00:53:20.060
because this

00:53:20.060 --> 00:53:22.060
manager that

00:53:22.060 --> 00:53:24.060
was looking after,

00:53:24.060 --> 00:53:26.060
who was a boss, was giving

00:53:26.060 --> 00:53:28.060
me a bit of trouble before the

00:53:28.060 --> 00:53:30.060
Atwoods actually left.

00:53:30.060 --> 00:53:32.060
And I tried to go to Sonny's in

00:53:32.060 --> 00:53:34.060
those days.

00:53:34.060 --> 00:53:36.060
When I was 34

00:53:36.060 --> 00:53:38.060
I tried to get out then.

00:53:38.060 --> 00:53:40.060
But I stuck it out.

00:53:40.060 --> 00:53:42.060
Right. So

00:53:42.060 --> 00:53:44.060
you said that the Atwoods,

00:53:44.060 --> 00:53:46.060
were they good bosses?

00:53:46.060 --> 00:53:48.060
I found them very good.

00:53:48.060 --> 00:53:50.060
I know I had a few issues

00:53:50.060 --> 00:53:52.060
with the tiar and that.

00:53:52.060 --> 00:53:54.060
But no, they were really

00:53:54.060 --> 00:53:56.060
kind.

00:53:56.060 --> 00:53:58.060
Although they didn't pay you?

00:53:58.060 --> 00:54:00.060
No, they didn't have

00:54:00.060 --> 00:54:02.060
the money. They say

00:54:02.060 --> 00:54:04.060
they didn't.

00:54:04.060 --> 00:54:06.060
There we are, who knows.

00:54:06.060 --> 00:54:10.060
So you were very fond,

00:54:10.060 --> 00:54:12.060
I mean you thought they treated you well?

00:54:12.060 --> 00:54:14.060
I thought they were wonderful.

00:54:14.060 --> 00:54:16.060
Could I just ask you then,

00:54:16.060 --> 00:54:18.060
did you get a pension or anything

00:54:18.060 --> 00:54:20.060
like that? I had

00:54:20.060 --> 00:54:22.060
a private pension.

00:54:22.060 --> 00:54:24.060
And I had to wait for the old

00:54:24.060 --> 00:54:26.060
age pensioner

00:54:26.060 --> 00:54:28.060
when I was 60. But I had

00:54:28.060 --> 00:54:30.060
nothing before it.

00:54:30.060 --> 00:54:32.060
I had problems

00:54:32.060 --> 00:54:34.060
with

00:54:34.060 --> 00:54:36.060
disability living allowance.

00:54:36.060 --> 00:54:38.060
And the social

00:54:38.060 --> 00:54:40.060
worker had to

00:54:40.060 --> 00:54:42.060
help me out because

00:54:42.060 --> 00:54:44.060
it wasn't coming forward.

00:54:44.060 --> 00:54:46.060
So it was difficult till

00:54:46.060 --> 00:54:48.060
they gave me

00:54:48.060 --> 00:54:50.060
disability

00:54:50.060 --> 00:54:52.060
living allowance. So there was no pension

00:54:52.060 --> 00:54:54.060
from the factory? No.

00:54:54.060 --> 00:54:56.060
Do you know how much the other workers were paid? Were you all

00:54:56.060 --> 00:54:58.060
paid the same, do you think?

00:54:58.060 --> 00:55:00.060
All the girls were, yes.

00:55:00.060 --> 00:55:02.060
But all the men, no. They had

00:55:02.060 --> 00:55:04.060
a lot more than the women.

00:55:04.060 --> 00:55:06.060
Any of us really could have

00:55:06.060 --> 00:55:08.060
done their jobs because we were

00:55:08.060 --> 00:55:10.060
doing some of their work.

00:55:10.060 --> 00:55:12.060
Did you have to

00:55:12.060 --> 00:55:14.060
share your wages with your

00:55:14.060 --> 00:55:16.060
family? I did, yes.

00:55:16.060 --> 00:55:18.060
I was,

00:55:18.060 --> 00:55:20.060
we had acquired this

00:55:20.060 --> 00:55:22.060
house, so the

00:55:22.060 --> 00:55:24.060
mortgage was quite

00:55:24.060 --> 00:55:26.060
high. And

00:55:26.060 --> 00:55:28.060
my father had died before

00:55:28.060 --> 00:55:30.060
he could start paying for it.

00:55:30.060 --> 00:55:32.060
This was in 83-ish.

00:55:32.060 --> 00:55:34.060
He'd gone

00:55:34.060 --> 00:55:36.060
ill before.

00:55:36.060 --> 00:55:38.060
And he couldn't get any money off the

00:55:38.060 --> 00:55:40.060
estate because

00:55:40.060 --> 00:55:42.060
he was self-employed.

00:55:42.060 --> 00:55:44.060
And why did he have £200

00:55:44.060 --> 00:55:46.060
in the bank? And he said,

00:55:46.060 --> 00:55:48.060
well, I have to pay my

00:55:48.060 --> 00:55:50.060
material and I have to pay

00:55:50.060 --> 00:55:52.060
the rent because we hadn't

00:55:52.060 --> 00:55:54.060
quite acquired the house.

00:55:54.060 --> 00:55:56.060
But when he died, I had to take the mortgage

00:55:56.060 --> 00:55:58.060
on by myself

00:55:58.060 --> 00:56:00.060
because my brother hadn't got

00:56:00.060 --> 00:56:02.060
a job because he was working with my father

00:56:02.060 --> 00:56:04.060
and he didn't know what he was going to do.

00:56:04.060 --> 00:56:06.060
And my mother didn't have a job.

00:56:06.060 --> 00:56:08.060
So I had

00:56:08.060 --> 00:56:10.060
to take on. And were you paying

00:56:10.060 --> 00:56:12.060
from, you know, from the, as,

00:56:12.060 --> 00:56:14.060
were you paying

00:56:14.060 --> 00:56:16.060
from when you started working in the factory?

00:56:16.060 --> 00:56:18.060
Were you giving your mother?

00:56:18.060 --> 00:56:20.060
Oh, yes. Even from the day that I was

00:56:20.060 --> 00:56:22.060
15, a Saturday girl,

00:56:22.060 --> 00:56:24.060
even when I was 11 years old,

00:56:24.060 --> 00:56:26.060
babysitting,

00:56:26.060 --> 00:56:28.060
I was contributing

00:56:28.060 --> 00:56:30.060
my money to her.

00:56:30.060 --> 00:56:32.060
What did you do? You, presumably,

00:56:32.060 --> 00:56:34.060
you kept some money to yourself.

00:56:34.060 --> 00:56:36.060
So what did you spend your money

00:56:36.060 --> 00:56:38.060
on? Either

00:56:38.060 --> 00:56:40.060
making my clothes on material

00:56:40.060 --> 00:56:42.060
so that I didn't have to buy

00:56:42.060 --> 00:56:44.060
clothes, my daughter,

00:56:44.060 --> 00:56:46.060
basically, my money

00:56:46.060 --> 00:56:48.060
went on my daughter.

00:56:48.060 --> 00:56:50.060
But I did have a sister

00:56:50.060 --> 00:56:52.060
who had lost her husband

00:56:52.060 --> 00:56:54.060
and she had two young children

00:56:54.060 --> 00:56:56.060
and I was contributing, helping

00:56:56.060 --> 00:56:58.060
her. So every penny

00:56:58.060 --> 00:57:00.060
was dished out.

00:57:00.060 --> 00:57:02.060
Right, right.

00:57:02.060 --> 00:57:04.060
So did you spend,

00:57:04.060 --> 00:57:06.060
did you spend some on records,

00:57:06.060 --> 00:57:08.060
you said? Oh, yes. I loved my records.

00:57:08.060 --> 00:57:10.060
I loved tapes,

00:57:10.060 --> 00:57:12.060
but I used to copy

00:57:12.060 --> 00:57:14.060
off the tapes,

00:57:14.060 --> 00:57:16.060
off the television, whatever.

00:57:16.060 --> 00:57:18.060
I copied them so I didn't have

00:57:18.060 --> 00:57:20.060
to spend any

00:57:20.060 --> 00:57:22.060
extra money.

00:57:22.060 --> 00:57:24.060
So did you have

00:57:24.060 --> 00:57:26.060
any help with your,

00:57:26.060 --> 00:57:28.060
I know your mum helped you

00:57:28.060 --> 00:57:30.060
look after your daughter. Did you have any other

00:57:30.060 --> 00:57:32.060
financial help? No.

00:57:32.060 --> 00:57:34.060
All I had was the money coming from

00:57:34.060 --> 00:57:36.060
the factory. You had,

00:57:36.060 --> 00:57:38.060
in those days, you had to produce

00:57:38.060 --> 00:57:40.060
12 documents

00:57:40.060 --> 00:57:42.060
so that you could have a little bit extra

00:57:42.060 --> 00:57:44.060
and you had the family allowance.

00:57:44.060 --> 00:57:46.060
But every 12 weeks you had to declare

00:57:46.060 --> 00:57:48.060
what you were working,

00:57:48.060 --> 00:57:50.060
how much, and then they would assess

00:57:50.060 --> 00:57:52.060
you and give you a bit extra.

00:57:52.060 --> 00:57:54.060
So you didn't have any help

00:57:54.060 --> 00:57:56.060
from the father? No,

00:57:56.060 --> 00:57:58.060
no. Right, okay.

00:57:58.060 --> 00:58:04.060
Did you have any perks from working in the factory?

00:58:04.060 --> 00:58:06.060
Yeah. Right, tell me.

00:58:06.060 --> 00:58:08.060
Well, they give you staff sales,

00:58:08.060 --> 00:58:10.060
which was sometimes what they

00:58:10.060 --> 00:58:12.060
couldn't send out,

00:58:12.060 --> 00:58:14.060
but we knew how to fix them

00:58:14.060 --> 00:58:16.060
and we put them right.

00:58:16.060 --> 00:58:18.060
What are the perks?

00:58:18.060 --> 00:58:20.060
Oh, I loved Christmases

00:58:20.060 --> 00:58:22.060
with them. I enjoyed them.

00:58:24.060 --> 00:58:26.060
I could,

00:58:26.060 --> 00:58:28.060
I can't think of anything else.

00:58:28.060 --> 00:58:30.060
Well, tell me about,

00:58:30.060 --> 00:58:32.060
did you have a Christmas party

00:58:32.060 --> 00:58:34.060
or something like that? Oh, every year,

00:58:34.060 --> 00:58:36.060
unless there was a problem

00:58:36.060 --> 00:58:38.060
with the finance, like

00:58:38.060 --> 00:58:40.060
the power cuts and that.

00:58:40.060 --> 00:58:42.060
If they couldn't do it,

00:58:42.060 --> 00:58:44.060
they used to say, especially Doug

00:58:44.060 --> 00:58:46.060
and Horace, we couldn't do a party this year,

00:58:46.060 --> 00:58:48.060
we're sorry, but it was very

00:58:48.060 --> 00:58:50.060
rarely. We'd go to the

00:58:50.060 --> 00:58:52.060
Porthcotell was the first time

00:58:52.060 --> 00:58:54.060
I went with them.

00:58:54.060 --> 00:58:56.060
The Espermaid Hotel.

00:58:56.060 --> 00:58:58.060
I'm not sure about the Seabank.

00:58:58.060 --> 00:59:00.060
And we went to

00:59:00.060 --> 00:59:02.060
the Manor Suite.

00:59:02.060 --> 00:59:04.060
And we also went to

00:59:04.060 --> 00:59:06.060
the Stonely Club.

00:59:06.060 --> 00:59:08.060
Oh, wonderful days.

00:59:08.060 --> 00:59:10.060
We didn't pay for them.

00:59:10.060 --> 00:59:12.060
We had whatever they put on.

00:59:12.060 --> 00:59:14.060
Sometimes it was a good meal

00:59:14.060 --> 00:59:16.060
or just chicken and chips in a basket.

00:59:16.060 --> 00:59:18.060
I was going to ask you, was it,

00:59:18.060 --> 00:59:20.060
what kind of thing was it?

00:59:20.060 --> 00:59:22.060
Just describe a party

00:59:22.060 --> 00:59:24.060
to me then.

00:59:24.060 --> 00:59:26.060
Well, in the Espermaid, we had a meal,

00:59:26.060 --> 00:59:28.060
a turkey dinner,

00:59:28.060 --> 00:59:30.060
a soup first, turkey

00:59:30.060 --> 00:59:32.060
after and afters afters.

00:59:32.060 --> 00:59:34.060
And each girl

00:59:34.060 --> 00:59:36.060
either may have had a box

00:59:36.060 --> 00:59:38.060
of chocolates, sorry, each of us

00:59:38.060 --> 00:59:40.060
would have a box of chocolates

00:59:40.060 --> 00:59:42.060
because I remember that.

00:59:42.060 --> 00:59:44.060
Or we'd have a raffle ticket

00:59:44.060 --> 00:59:46.060
and we'd have

00:59:46.060 --> 00:59:48.060
whatever jewellery he

00:59:48.060 --> 00:59:50.060
wants to give us.

00:59:50.060 --> 00:59:52.060
They weren't

00:59:54.060 --> 00:59:56.060
seconds, they were

00:59:56.060 --> 00:59:58.060
the best.

00:59:58.060 --> 01:00:00.060
Lovely. Do you remember what

01:00:00.060 --> 01:00:02.060
things you were given?

01:00:02.060 --> 01:00:04.060
No, not an offhand.

01:00:04.060 --> 01:00:06.060
No.

01:00:06.060 --> 01:00:08.060
Was there like a dance

01:00:08.060 --> 01:00:10.060
or something afterwards?

01:00:10.060 --> 01:00:12.060
Oh yes, discos. Oh, wonderful times, discos.

01:00:12.060 --> 01:00:14.060
I remember the night's arms

01:00:14.060 --> 01:00:16.060
because we must have gone to the night's arms

01:00:16.060 --> 01:00:18.060
up there and we had wonderful times.

01:00:18.060 --> 01:00:20.060
But one time when I was in

01:00:20.060 --> 01:00:22.060
the Stoney Club, the designer

01:00:22.060 --> 01:00:24.060
curled at me

01:00:24.060 --> 01:00:26.060
and I was on the floor trying to tell him,

01:00:26.060 --> 01:00:28.060
no, I don't want to go. And he dragged

01:00:28.060 --> 01:00:30.060
me up the steps to get on the stage

01:00:30.060 --> 01:00:32.060
and I didn't want to dance with him.

01:00:32.060 --> 01:00:34.060
I did not want him.

01:00:34.060 --> 01:00:36.060
It was great.

01:00:36.060 --> 01:00:38.060
Because I used to work in the Stoney

01:00:38.060 --> 01:00:40.060
and I loved the Stoney because

01:00:40.060 --> 01:00:42.060
I had discos going on up there.

01:00:42.060 --> 01:00:44.060
What's the Stoney?

01:00:44.060 --> 01:00:46.060
Right, the Stoney was a club

01:00:46.060 --> 01:00:48.060
where you had artists

01:00:48.060 --> 01:00:50.060
like Rolf Harris.

01:00:50.060 --> 01:00:52.060
Rolf Harris and

01:00:52.060 --> 01:00:54.060
Gary Glitter falling down

01:00:54.060 --> 01:00:56.060
the steps in his high shoes.

01:00:58.060 --> 01:01:00.060
What's his name? Slade.

01:01:02.060 --> 01:01:04.060
Tony Christie.

01:01:04.060 --> 01:01:06.060
This is the way to Amarillo.

01:01:08.060 --> 01:01:10.060
Jean Pitney.

01:01:10.060 --> 01:01:12.060
And Tommy Cooper.

01:01:12.060 --> 01:01:14.060
He was off stage

01:01:14.060 --> 01:01:16.060
and he had to have a drink before he came on stage.

01:01:18.060 --> 01:01:20.060
I don't know how he got through

01:01:20.060 --> 01:01:22.060
his little gate.

01:01:22.060 --> 01:01:24.060
He had a little gate going in and out of his little gate.

01:01:26.060 --> 01:01:28.060
And Norman Wisdom.

01:01:28.060 --> 01:01:30.060
Oh, Norman Wisdom.

01:01:30.060 --> 01:01:32.060
And I used to see him at the back of the stage

01:01:32.060 --> 01:01:34.060
and have autographs.

01:01:34.060 --> 01:01:36.060
I got a couple of photographs

01:01:36.060 --> 01:01:38.060
and I got, as I said,

01:01:38.060 --> 01:01:40.060
Jean Pitney,

01:01:40.060 --> 01:01:42.060
Rolf Harris, Tony Christie

01:01:42.060 --> 01:01:44.060
and one other.

01:01:44.060 --> 01:01:46.060
Des O'Connor.

01:01:46.060 --> 01:01:48.060
Des O'Connor.

01:01:48.060 --> 01:01:50.060
Des O'Connor.

01:01:52.060 --> 01:01:54.060
He changed his jumper to

01:01:54.060 --> 01:01:56.060
match mine because I was all in black

01:01:56.060 --> 01:01:58.060
and I had a yellowy,

01:01:58.060 --> 01:02:00.060
orangey cardigan on

01:02:00.060 --> 01:02:02.060
because I was always cold.

01:02:02.060 --> 01:02:04.060
And he changed his top

01:02:04.060 --> 01:02:08.060
to take a photograph.

01:02:08.060 --> 01:02:10.060
So this was, you used to work,

01:02:10.060 --> 01:02:12.060
this was one of your second jobs,

01:02:12.060 --> 01:02:14.060
so you saw these people

01:02:14.060 --> 01:02:16.060
when you worked there.

01:02:16.060 --> 01:02:18.060
What did you do there?

01:02:18.060 --> 01:02:20.060
I was a waitress but I also used to,

01:02:20.060 --> 01:02:22.060
I was taught in the Royal Oak,

01:02:22.060 --> 01:02:24.060
which is not far from here,

01:02:24.060 --> 01:02:26.060
how to work behind the bar.

01:02:26.060 --> 01:02:28.060
So when they found out, I could do both jobs.

01:02:30.060 --> 01:02:32.060
But the night that Bob Monkhouse

01:02:32.060 --> 01:02:34.060
was there,

01:02:34.060 --> 01:02:36.060
he had piano

01:02:36.060 --> 01:02:38.060
and all the lights went out.

01:02:38.060 --> 01:02:40.060
We blew the fuse in the kitchen

01:02:40.060 --> 01:02:42.060
doing Christmas puddings.

01:02:42.060 --> 01:02:44.060
And it was a big machine

01:02:44.060 --> 01:02:46.060
and he was still playing

01:02:46.060 --> 01:02:48.060
in the dark and I was

01:02:48.060 --> 01:02:50.060
behind the bar.

01:02:50.060 --> 01:02:52.060
I loved that.

01:02:52.060 --> 01:02:54.060
And I was also in the rugby club.

01:02:54.060 --> 01:02:56.060
Yes.

01:02:56.060 --> 01:02:58.060
I loved that place.

01:02:58.060 --> 01:03:00.060
I met Gareth Edwards,

01:03:00.060 --> 01:03:02.060
Rupert Moon

01:03:02.060 --> 01:03:04.060
and the Welsh

01:03:04.060 --> 01:03:06.060
referees,

01:03:06.060 --> 01:03:08.060
two of them,

01:03:08.060 --> 01:03:10.060
from North, is it North?

01:03:10.060 --> 01:03:12.060
I can't remember his name.

01:03:12.060 --> 01:03:14.060
One of the way back ones,

01:03:14.060 --> 01:03:16.060
when Gareth Edwards

01:03:16.060 --> 01:03:18.060
was around.

01:03:18.060 --> 01:03:20.060
But I sat on Gareth Edwards' lap

01:03:20.060 --> 01:03:22.060
and I also sat on

01:03:22.060 --> 01:03:24.060
Rupert Moon in the manor suite.

01:03:24.060 --> 01:03:26.060
But I also met one

01:03:26.060 --> 01:03:28.060
in the stony

01:03:28.060 --> 01:03:30.060
and he was on

01:03:30.060 --> 01:03:32.060
upstairs and downstairs.

01:03:32.060 --> 01:03:34.060
He was one of the

01:03:34.060 --> 01:03:36.060
butlers.

01:03:36.060 --> 01:03:38.060
He was in the club.

01:03:38.060 --> 01:03:40.060
So you enjoyed that.

01:03:40.060 --> 01:03:42.060
I did.

01:03:48.060 --> 01:03:50.060
So tell me then,

01:03:50.060 --> 01:03:52.060
holidays,

01:03:52.060 --> 01:03:54.060
what holidays did you have every year?

01:03:54.060 --> 01:03:56.060
I had two weeks a year

01:03:56.060 --> 01:03:58.060
but I didn't go anywhere

01:03:58.060 --> 01:04:00.060
unless I

01:04:00.060 --> 01:04:02.060
didn't have any work because I would work

01:04:02.060 --> 01:04:04.060
anywhere on my holidays.

01:04:04.060 --> 01:04:06.060
Didn't matter where.

01:04:06.060 --> 01:04:08.060
But I did go to London with my

01:04:08.060 --> 01:04:10.060
daughter for days.

01:04:10.060 --> 01:04:12.060
I also

01:04:12.060 --> 01:04:14.060
went to Blackpool with her

01:04:14.060 --> 01:04:16.060
twice to Blackpool.

01:04:16.060 --> 01:04:18.060
But what about

01:04:18.060 --> 01:04:20.060
the holidays?

01:04:20.060 --> 01:04:22.060
Did you all take

01:04:22.060 --> 01:04:24.060
time off at the same time, like the

01:04:24.060 --> 01:04:26.060
miners' holiday or did they

01:04:26.060 --> 01:04:28.060
shut the factory down?

01:04:28.060 --> 01:04:30.060
They used to shut the factory down

01:04:30.060 --> 01:04:32.060
in August I believe it was.

01:04:32.060 --> 01:04:34.060
Right.

01:04:34.060 --> 01:04:36.060
But you used to stay at home.

01:04:36.060 --> 01:04:38.060
Anyway, why go anywhere

01:04:38.060 --> 01:04:40.060
if you live in Puthcall, isn't it?

01:04:40.060 --> 01:04:42.060
Yes, it's wonderful, yeah.

01:04:42.060 --> 01:04:44.060
It was like going to Blackpool.

01:04:44.060 --> 01:04:46.060
That was like home from home.

01:04:46.060 --> 01:04:48.060
Yes.

01:04:48.060 --> 01:04:50.060
And there's more entertainment there.

01:04:50.060 --> 01:04:52.060
More lights.

01:04:54.060 --> 01:04:56.060
Did you have to clock in when you worked?

01:04:56.060 --> 01:04:58.060
Yes, I had to clock in

01:04:58.060 --> 01:05:00.060
and I had to be there before the clock

01:05:00.060 --> 01:05:02.060
went at eight o'clock.

01:05:02.060 --> 01:05:04.060
And then I wasn't allowed to clock it out until

01:05:04.060 --> 01:05:06.060
the clock said

01:05:06.060 --> 01:05:08.060
four or five because we did have

01:05:08.060 --> 01:05:10.060
different hours earlier

01:05:10.060 --> 01:05:12.060
later on in the factory.

01:05:12.060 --> 01:05:14.060
Right, so how many hours did you

01:05:14.060 --> 01:05:16.060
work at the beginning and then

01:05:16.060 --> 01:05:18.060
how did they change?

01:05:18.060 --> 01:05:20.060
I believe it was

01:05:20.060 --> 01:05:22.060
maybe 39

01:05:22.060 --> 01:05:24.060
or was it more

01:05:24.060 --> 01:05:26.060
because it was like eight or five

01:05:26.060 --> 01:05:28.060
and on a Friday

01:05:28.060 --> 01:05:30.060
it was like eight till twelve o'clock.

01:05:32.060 --> 01:05:34.060
The hours were cut down

01:05:34.060 --> 01:05:36.060
like an hour every day

01:05:36.060 --> 01:05:38.060
till it was eight till four.

01:05:38.060 --> 01:05:40.060
So did you

01:05:40.060 --> 01:05:42.060
have a lunch hour?

01:05:42.060 --> 01:05:44.060
Yes, it was half an hour.

01:05:44.060 --> 01:05:46.060
And that didn't change, did it?

01:05:46.060 --> 01:05:48.060
No.

01:05:48.060 --> 01:05:50.060
And did you have a canteen in there?

01:05:50.060 --> 01:05:52.060
Yes, but I never used it.

01:05:52.060 --> 01:05:54.060
I always used to go up to the shops to get

01:05:54.060 --> 01:05:56.060
my mother's food or whatever

01:05:56.060 --> 01:05:58.060
was needed in the lunch hour.

01:05:58.060 --> 01:06:00.060
Or I'd come home and cut the hedge

01:06:00.060 --> 01:06:02.060
or cut the grass.

01:06:02.060 --> 01:06:04.060
Never stopped then, did you?

01:06:04.060 --> 01:06:06.060
No.

01:06:06.060 --> 01:06:08.060
Right.

01:06:08.060 --> 01:06:10.060
And did you have breaks

01:06:10.060 --> 01:06:12.060
as well? Yes, it was only ten minutes

01:06:12.060 --> 01:06:14.060
break.

01:06:14.060 --> 01:06:16.060
And did you go to the canteen for your breaks? Yes.

01:06:16.060 --> 01:06:18.060
In those days when I was with the Atwoods

01:06:18.060 --> 01:06:20.060
I used to bring in pasties

01:06:20.060 --> 01:06:22.060
from Elizabeth's shop

01:06:22.060 --> 01:06:24.060
in New Road.

01:06:24.060 --> 01:06:26.060
And we'd have pasties and a cup of tea.

01:06:26.060 --> 01:06:28.060
And then when that

01:06:28.060 --> 01:06:30.060
shop went

01:06:30.060 --> 01:06:32.060
we used to have

01:06:32.060 --> 01:06:34.060
food there, which was like a

01:06:34.060 --> 01:06:36.060
Kit Kat or a biscuit

01:06:36.060 --> 01:06:38.060
and a cup of tea.

01:06:38.060 --> 01:06:40.060
Maybe toast.

01:06:40.060 --> 01:06:42.060
Was that enough? Do you think there was

01:06:42.060 --> 01:06:44.060
enough breaks?

01:06:44.060 --> 01:06:46.060
Was it exhausting the day?

01:06:46.060 --> 01:06:48.060
You had no choice.

01:06:48.060 --> 01:06:50.060
That was it.

